WEBVTT

00:00.001 --> 00:25.002
<b><font color="#49fff7">Synced By: Luis-Subs
Improved By: Fidel33</font></b>

01:15.158 --> 01:17.227
(WHEELS RUMBLING OVER CONCRETE)

01:17.327 --> 01:19.078
(BELLS CHIMING)

01:27.003 --> 01:29.630
(THUNDER RUMBLING)

01:48.817 --> 01:51.151
(AIR WHOOSHING AND BELLS JINGLING)

01:52.362 --> 01:55.364
♪ (BING CROSBY AND
THE ANDREWS SISTERS SINGING) ♪

01:55.698 --> 01:57.267
♪ Here comes Santa Claus ♪

01:57.367 --> 01:58.768
♪ Here comes Santa Claus ♪

01:58.868 --> 02:01.829
♪ Riding down Santa Claus Lane ♪

02:02.205 --> 02:04.858
♪ Vixen and Blitzen and all his reindeer ♪

02:04.958 --> 02:06.818
♪ Are pulling on the reins... ♪

02:06.918 --> 02:08.695
WOMAN: (ON RADIO) Just two
shopping days left till Christmas

02:08.794 --> 02:10.780
and traffic is looking good
in the centre of town.

02:10.880 --> 02:13.116
Victoria Embankment is moving
smoothly in both directions.

02:13.216 --> 02:16.745
There does seem to be some sort
of hold up over Tower Bridge.

02:16.845 --> 02:19.873
I can see queues
on all approaches to it.

02:19.973 --> 02:24.169
There appears to be livestock.
No... It's reindeer.

02:24.269 --> 02:27.464
Reindeer! I repeat, reindeer,
running wild over Tower Bridge.

02:27.564 --> 02:33.277
♪ He's got a bag that is filled with toys
for the boys and girls again ♪

02:33.403 --> 02:36.848
♪ Hear those sleigh bells jingle jangle ♪

02:36.948 --> 02:38.907
♪ What a beautiful sight ♪

02:39.742 --> 02:42.979
♪ Jump in bed, cover up your head ♪

02:43.079 --> 02:46.316
♪ 'Cause Santa Claus comes tonight
Tonight ♪

02:46.416 --> 02:49.861
♪ Santa Claus comes tonight
Happy Days... ♪

02:49.961 --> 02:51.613
MAN: (ON RADIO) A surprising story today.

02:51.713 --> 02:55.909
We have reports of reindeer running loose
on the streets of London.

02:56.009 --> 02:57.494
♪ Here comes Santa Claus ♪

02:57.594 --> 02:59.079
♪ Here comes Santa Claus ♪

02:59.179 --> 03:01.430
♪ Riding down Santa Claus Lane ♪

03:02.140 --> 03:05.460
♪ He doesn't care
if you're rich or poor, boy ♪

03:05.560 --> 03:08.103
♪ He loves you just the same ♪

03:08.438 --> 03:11.481
♪ Santa knows that
we're God's children... ♪

03:11.774 --> 03:14.193
Right...

03:14.611 --> 03:16.820
Mobile phone.

03:18.281 --> 03:20.115
One Rubik's cube.

03:21.784 --> 03:23.285
Oh... Unsolved.

03:23.620 --> 03:26.622
And one set of car keys.

03:26.956 --> 03:28.415
Sign there.

03:29.876 --> 03:33.045
- That your Tom, is it?
- Yeah, that was him two years ago.

03:33.963 --> 03:36.131
- Takes after you.
- Well, let's hope not.

03:37.759 --> 03:39.494
WOMAN: (ON TV) More now on our top story

03:39.594 --> 03:42.080
of the reindeer running loose
on the streets of London.

03:42.180 --> 03:45.515
There have been sightings
as far west as Ealing Broadway.

03:45.642 --> 03:47.377
No-one knows where they came from,

03:47.477 --> 03:50.004
so let's just hope
they're not Santa's reindeer,

03:50.104 --> 03:53.232
or there'll be a lot of disappointed
children this Christmas.

04:00.156 --> 04:02.308
Hey, quick! We have to stop the train!

04:02.408 --> 04:03.893
There are people on board!

04:03.993 --> 04:06.479
- We can't. The brakes have failed.
- Well, we have to.

04:06.579 --> 04:08.523
TOM: There's an old lady
stuck in the back seat!

04:08.623 --> 04:10.749
TONY: An old lady? Oh, no!

04:11.417 --> 04:13.695
But don't worry, she just made it out.

04:13.795 --> 04:17.089
TOM: No, the old lady got really
mangled up. She's in a mess.

04:17.673 --> 04:19.466
An old lady? Really?

04:19.676 --> 04:22.579
Ah! My legs! I can't feel my legs!

04:22.679 --> 04:26.139
Ah, but fortunately
there's an ambulance nearby.

04:26.266 --> 04:29.059
Nee-nah! Nee-nah!
And it saves the old lady's life.

04:29.269 --> 04:32.854
No, she's dead. She had a big cut
on her leg and bled out.

04:33.606 --> 04:36.858
(COUGHING AND SPLUTTERING)

04:37.193 --> 04:39.695
(COUGHING AGAIN)

04:43.533 --> 04:46.493
(CHOKING)

04:47.787 --> 04:50.914
Well, I hope all this death
and destruction's making you hungry.

04:51.040 --> 04:52.916
(PHONE RINGS)

04:53.543 --> 04:55.585
- Hello?
- STEVE: Hello. It's me.

04:56.838 --> 04:58.046
Hang on.

04:59.799 --> 05:01.951
Come on, Tom, let's play something else.

05:02.051 --> 05:03.969
- Are you out?
- STEVE: I'm out.

05:05.263 --> 05:07.848
- I'm pleased for you.
- Yeah, I'm pleased for me too.

05:08.766 --> 05:10.267
- How are you?
- I'm good.

05:10.643 --> 05:14.730
Uh, so, listen, I was just wondering
if I could pop by later

05:15.148 --> 05:16.940
and see Tom, if that's all right?

05:17.066 --> 05:19.401
- No, today's not a good day.
- Ah, come on, Ali.

05:19.569 --> 05:22.571
You can't just change the plans cos you
have something better to do tomorrow.

05:22.739 --> 05:24.740
No, I haven't got anything better to do.

05:25.533 --> 05:27.534
Well, we'll see you then. I've gotta go.

05:28.328 --> 05:31.246
All right. Thank... Thank you.

05:33.333 --> 05:34.791
Was that Dad?

05:36.002 --> 05:38.920
- Yeah, that was Steve.
- Why didn't you let him come over?

05:39.088 --> 05:40.823
Because you'll have more time
with him tomorrow.

05:40.923 --> 05:43.425
- What if he doesn't come tomorrow?
- He will.

05:43.551 --> 05:46.386
He won't if you're being
horrible to him.

05:47.513 --> 05:48.764
Tom...

05:53.936 --> 05:56.229
(DOOR SHUTS)

06:06.366 --> 06:09.618
(FAINT ASTRONAUT RADIO CHATTER)

06:31.307 --> 06:33.642
TONY: Just try and give him
the benefit of the doubt.

06:33.810 --> 06:36.796
I'm just scared he's gonna build Tom up
with promises and then let him down.

06:36.896 --> 06:39.106
TONY: Everybody deserves
a second chance.

06:39.857 --> 06:42.442
- ALI: Steve's had about 12.
- TONY: I know.

06:42.944 --> 06:45.278
TONY: Let's just try and have
a nice Christmas.

07:02.880 --> 07:05.173
(CROAKING)

07:05.716 --> 07:07.509
(BUZZING)

07:08.010 --> 07:10.971
Don't you like the fly?
Will you have a little grub?

07:11.180 --> 07:13.640
- (KNOCKING)
- Come in.

07:15.685 --> 07:17.227
(CROAKING)

07:17.353 --> 07:22.065
Mr Anderson, do take a seat.
No? Don't want a fly?

07:29.198 --> 07:30.699
(CROAKS)

07:32.410 --> 07:35.120
- Mince pie?
- Er, no, thank you.

07:38.249 --> 07:40.667
Do you understand what my job is?

07:41.169 --> 07:44.212
Yeah, it's to make sure that I don't
fall back into a life of crime.

07:44.380 --> 07:48.049
Yeah. Hmm. It's also
to catch you when you do.

07:48.426 --> 07:51.344
- And I will catch you.
- I'm not gonna do anything wrong.

07:53.055 --> 07:55.583
- I'm sure you hear that all the time.
- All the time.

07:55.683 --> 07:58.810
- But this time it's true.
- But this time it's true.

08:00.563 --> 08:03.299
I want you, for the next two months,
to come to this office

08:03.399 --> 08:07.637
every day at 5:00, starting tomorrow,
excluding Christmas Day.

08:07.737 --> 08:09.237
Is that clear?

08:09.906 --> 08:12.475
Miss an appointment
and I'll assume you're stealing,

08:12.575 --> 08:14.143
and I'll send you back to prison.

08:14.243 --> 08:17.063
Er, just for the record, I wasn't actually
at the stealing end of the business.

08:17.163 --> 08:19.289
- I was the getaway driver.
- Oh.

08:20.958 --> 08:23.502
That's right.
You were the getaway driver...

08:23.753 --> 08:27.380
Who didn't get away. (CHUCKLING)

08:29.091 --> 08:30.634
(CHUCKLING)

08:30.801 --> 08:32.552
(CRUNCHING)

08:35.765 --> 08:37.015
(BUZZING)

08:40.770 --> 08:42.062
(BUZZING)

08:42.188 --> 08:43.980
(GULPING AND BUZZING)

08:44.232 --> 08:46.509
(BUZZING)

08:46.609 --> 08:47.651
(GULPS)

08:51.906 --> 08:54.157
Is there any reason
why you are still here?

08:55.201 --> 08:56.243
No.

09:41.330 --> 09:43.582
(THUDS)

10:12.194 --> 10:13.570
(DOG HOWLING)

10:32.632 --> 10:34.507
(DOOR CREAKS OPEN)

10:40.598 --> 10:42.849
(SNORING)

10:45.353 --> 10:46.519
Hello?

10:51.942 --> 10:53.109
Hello!

10:57.365 --> 10:58.698
My letter.

11:00.159 --> 11:01.894
Argh!

11:01.994 --> 11:04.245
- Oh!
- (CLATTERING)

11:04.413 --> 11:06.706
Oh! Ooh!

11:08.751 --> 11:12.045
Ooh, ooh! Ahhh!

11:16.425 --> 11:18.468
Ho, ho, ho!

11:19.095 --> 11:22.915
I've been old for a thousand years
and I'm not getting any younger.

11:23.015 --> 11:25.684
- Are you the real Santa?
- Why, yes!

11:27.269 --> 11:30.772
Shouldn't you be in Lapland,
sorting out everyone's toys?

11:30.940 --> 11:34.802
Sorting out toys, working out
flight paths, feeding reindeer.

11:34.902 --> 11:37.680
Loading, stowing, stacking,
labelling, cladding,

11:37.780 --> 11:39.640
packing, ribboning, wrapping,

11:39.740 --> 11:43.118
and that's before I even think about
turning the Northern Lights on.

11:44.870 --> 11:46.287
MAN: (ON TV) Arcs,

11:46.997 --> 11:50.125
but more like curtains of... Of green.

11:50.501 --> 11:51.986
It doesn't look to me like

11:52.086 --> 11:53.988
- it's cascading down.
- (PHONE RINGS)

11:54.088 --> 11:57.090
It looks like it's rising
up from the ground.

11:58.259 --> 11:59.426
(PHONE RINGING)

12:00.720 --> 12:03.221
- Hello?
- TOM: (WHISPERING) Hello.

12:05.307 --> 12:06.307
Tom?

12:06.726 --> 12:08.643
I can't talk loudly or Mum will hear.

12:09.019 --> 12:11.146
Hello, mate. How are you?
How are you doing?

12:11.772 --> 12:13.648
Santa's in the garage.

12:14.316 --> 12:15.442
What?

12:15.568 --> 12:18.278
TOM: He says that
we've got to help him get home.

12:18.821 --> 12:21.906
- He says he knows you.
- Are you in the garage with a man?

12:22.450 --> 12:25.785
No, I'm in the house.
Santa's in the garage.

12:26.120 --> 12:28.747
Okay, Tom,
can you put your mum on, please?

12:29.165 --> 12:30.540
TOM: No, I can't.

12:30.875 --> 12:32.818
Santa says it has to be you.

12:32.918 --> 12:34.236
STEVE: Tom, listen to me...

12:34.336 --> 12:37.505
He's crashed his sleigh, lost his
reindeer, and if we don't help him...

12:37.715 --> 12:42.093
- Tom, go and get your mother. Please.
- No. I'm going back to the garage.

12:42.511 --> 12:45.013
- Santa wants to show me his plan.
- Tom.

12:45.765 --> 12:47.390
Tom.

12:49.226 --> 12:51.019
(TYRES SCREECHING)

12:57.985 --> 13:00.846
I'm worried about the reindeer.
It's only natural.

13:00.946 --> 13:04.532
Prancer is the oldest... Steve!

13:04.867 --> 13:06.852
Who the hell are you?

13:06.952 --> 13:08.270
- What are you doing?
- Who are you?

13:08.370 --> 13:10.398
- You know who I am.
- I what?

13:10.498 --> 13:12.525
- You know who I am.
- I haven't got a clue who you are.

13:12.625 --> 13:14.083
He's Santa!

13:17.129 --> 13:20.241
Okay, just so we're clear, the only
reason I haven't knocked your block off

13:20.341 --> 13:22.535
is because of him, so whatever
your reason is for being here now

13:22.635 --> 13:24.412
it better be a good one.

13:24.512 --> 13:26.664
I was running in my new sleigh.

13:26.764 --> 13:29.500
I came in too low, hit a telephone wire,

13:29.600 --> 13:31.768
got thrown off and hit my head.

13:32.645 --> 13:33.728
Tom?

13:34.814 --> 13:39.067
He's lost his reindeer, and if he doesn't get
to Lapland, Christmas is off.

13:39.485 --> 13:40.970
All right, Tom.

13:41.070 --> 13:43.321
When your father was your age,
he saw me.

13:43.614 --> 13:46.699
- What are you talking about?
- It was Christmas Eve.

13:47.743 --> 13:50.453
You saw a shooting star
racing across the heavens.

13:51.747 --> 13:53.248
- That was me.
- Tom?

13:55.084 --> 13:57.252
- Tom, are you in there?
- We need to help him, Steve.

13:58.003 --> 14:00.547
- Tom, who are you talking to?
- Go on, you get out of here.

14:00.714 --> 14:03.967
- And don't you ever come back.
- Bye, Tom. Don't worry.

14:08.931 --> 14:10.431
Tom, inside.

14:13.310 --> 14:14.727
- Steve.
- Toby.

14:15.896 --> 14:17.564
It's... It's Tony.

14:18.440 --> 14:19.899
ALI: What is it, T?

14:21.944 --> 14:23.403
It's nothing.

14:23.904 --> 14:25.488
It's just a cat.

14:30.327 --> 14:31.494
(DOOR SHUTS)

14:32.621 --> 14:34.080
(DOGS BARKING)

14:50.598 --> 14:52.140
- Ooh!
- (THUDS)

14:52.558 --> 14:55.602
(CLATTERING)

14:55.978 --> 14:57.604
(DOGS BARKING)

15:05.821 --> 15:07.322
Hello, boys.

15:14.455 --> 15:15.538
Oh...

15:16.665 --> 15:17.707
Ooh.

15:18.000 --> 15:20.501
Ooh! Ooh, ooh.

15:26.634 --> 15:28.410
Ooh! Ooh!

15:28.510 --> 15:29.844
(CHUCKLES)

15:30.512 --> 15:31.747
Ooh!

15:31.847 --> 15:33.389
- Oh!
- (THUDS)

15:38.437 --> 15:39.812
(BARKING)

15:45.402 --> 15:47.179
(BARKING)

15:47.279 --> 15:50.198
Shh. Shh! It's me.

16:00.876 --> 16:03.252
There you are. You're all here.

16:03.379 --> 16:05.489
Thank goodness.
I was so worried about you.

16:05.589 --> 16:07.908
Antlers up. Who wants to go home?

16:08.008 --> 16:09.717
All of you? Right, leave it to me.

16:20.354 --> 16:23.064
Now, if I can just get them airborne...

16:25.985 --> 16:28.611
(SIREN WAILING)

16:39.581 --> 16:41.233
WOMAN: (ON TV) Toe tap right,
toe tap left.

16:41.333 --> 16:43.543
Swing the arms. Four more...

16:43.919 --> 16:46.322
MAN: (ON TV) This is the scene
from Sydney, Australia,

16:46.422 --> 16:49.090
where Christmas Eve begins
just like any other day.

16:49.216 --> 16:50.258
Big steps, count four.

16:51.927 --> 16:55.263
MAN: (ON TV) Yesterday we told you about
reindeer running over Tower Bridge,

16:55.389 --> 16:59.225
and now this festive story
has taken another mysterious twist.

16:59.768 --> 17:04.271
A man in his 60S, claiming to be
none other than Father Christmas,

17:04.772 --> 17:08.108
broke into Battersea Dogs Home,
where the reindeer are being housed,

17:08.609 --> 17:11.904
and tried to catapult them
over the fence.

17:12.614 --> 17:15.532
It looks like Santa will be
spending Christmas in prison.

17:15.951 --> 17:18.703
But don't worry, kids.
He's not the real Santa.

17:19.496 --> 17:23.290
How do we know?
Because Santa's reindeer can fly.

17:23.709 --> 17:25.376
(CAMERA CLICKING)

17:28.297 --> 17:29.297
Ten sticks of rock.

17:30.424 --> 17:32.467
As a matter of fact,
they're called candy canes.

17:33.761 --> 17:36.179
Ten sticks of rock.

17:38.515 --> 17:40.725
- Letters.
- Forty-one.

17:42.686 --> 17:44.062
Forty-one letters.

17:55.365 --> 17:58.242
(INMATES JEERING)

18:00.287 --> 18:03.164
INMATE #1: Oi, pops!
What am I getting for Christmas?

18:03.373 --> 18:05.234
INMATE #2: Send him
a letter like everyone else!

18:05.334 --> 18:07.668
All right, lads, leave it out.

18:08.212 --> 18:11.281
INMATE #3: Oi, Santa! Are you gonna
escape up the chimney?

18:11.381 --> 18:13.049
Eh? (CHUCKLING)

18:16.762 --> 18:20.056
Right, stop. This one. This one.

18:27.648 --> 18:29.591
I'd get changed if I was you.

18:29.691 --> 18:31.593
You can't keep me in here.

18:31.693 --> 18:33.069
Room not to your liking, sir?

18:33.570 --> 18:37.198
Oh, wait, I do apologise,
but all the sea-view rooms are taken.

18:37.866 --> 18:40.785
Officer, please,
this is very, very important.

18:40.953 --> 18:44.106
You have to let me out of here
or Christmas will be cancelled.

18:44.206 --> 18:45.832
(DOOR SLAMS SHUT)

18:50.420 --> 18:52.338
(SPLATTING ON WINDOW GRILL)

19:18.323 --> 19:19.740
Hello, mate.

19:24.538 --> 19:27.775
Take me to see Santa or I'm not coming.

19:27.875 --> 19:29.458
That's the deal. Take it or leave it.

19:30.252 --> 19:31.752
I'll take it.

19:40.220 --> 19:42.331
When are you going to
get rid of this old banger?

19:42.431 --> 19:44.724
Oh, now, now.
This old banger treated us well.

19:45.517 --> 19:47.935
- I made you both a packed lunch.
- Thank you.

19:48.604 --> 19:50.605
- Have fun.
- We will.

19:51.565 --> 19:52.899
Thank you.

19:57.613 --> 19:59.113
- Bye.
- (KISSES TOM)

19:59.948 --> 20:01.199
Love you.

20:05.454 --> 20:07.538
I'm sorry about last night.

20:10.459 --> 20:12.778
So, do you wanna go and see
Father Christmas?

20:12.878 --> 20:14.863
What do you say we swing by Harrods?

20:14.963 --> 20:16.631
Santa's in prison.

20:17.132 --> 20:20.702
What? No. No. We can't go and see
that old fruitcake from last night.

20:20.802 --> 20:21.870
He's not a fruitcake.

20:21.970 --> 20:24.248
Well, he's definitely a few fries short
of a Happy Meal.

20:24.348 --> 20:25.582
He's Santa.

20:25.682 --> 20:27.835
Look, Tom, I can't get us into prison
to go and see him.

20:27.935 --> 20:31.604
It's not possible. I'm sorry.
No, wait, wait, wait.

20:33.023 --> 20:34.315
There might be a way.

20:37.986 --> 20:40.655
Table six. You've got five minutes.

20:53.001 --> 20:54.585
Right, I'll tell you what.

20:55.003 --> 20:58.699
If I... When I prove
that he's not Father Christmas,

20:58.799 --> 21:02.093
can we just forget all of this
and have a nice day together? Mm?

21:02.886 --> 21:03.928
Okay.

21:04.596 --> 21:06.222
(DOOR OPENS)

21:09.101 --> 21:10.518
Oh.

21:14.022 --> 21:17.191
Thank you for coming.
This place is horrible.

21:17.317 --> 21:19.735
Yeah, well, it's not
a holiday camp, Nick.

21:20.988 --> 21:22.947
- You know my name.
- I worked it out.

21:23.365 --> 21:26.101
- How?
- Well, I thought of Saint Nicholas,

21:26.201 --> 21:28.452
and then I abbreviated it to Saint Nick.

21:28.787 --> 21:31.205
And then, I took away the "Saint".

21:31.373 --> 21:34.583
(CHUCKLES)
That's exactly how I came to it.

21:34.710 --> 21:36.153
Oh, wow! What do you know?

21:36.253 --> 21:39.297
I tried other more elaborate names,
but that one seemed to stick.

21:39.631 --> 21:42.550
- We've come to rescue you.
- Thank goodness.

21:42.843 --> 21:45.761
Yeah, we thought we'd free your
reindeer and fly in and pick you up.

21:46.138 --> 21:50.933
No, that wouldn't work because
the reindeer can't actually fly.

21:51.476 --> 21:55.021
I mean, not by themselves, but...
Well, it's complicated.

21:55.314 --> 21:58.592
But if you find the sleigh,
I mean, provided it's not broken,

21:58.692 --> 22:00.151
then you might be able to.

22:00.736 --> 22:02.403
Are you on medication?

22:03.655 --> 22:06.183
Or worse, are you not on medication?

22:06.283 --> 22:07.742
Ho, ho, ho!

22:08.076 --> 22:10.619
- You still don't believe I'm Santa.
- Do you wanna know why?

22:11.413 --> 22:14.457
- Because I'm 30.
- But once you were seven.

22:14.666 --> 22:17.752
Yeah, and I saw a shooting star.
Tell me something I don't know.

22:18.920 --> 22:21.255
It was an exceptionally cold
Christmas night.

22:22.549 --> 22:24.216
Your parents were drunk.
They'd been rowing.

22:24.426 --> 22:27.428
- My parents got divorced.
- This was their last Christmas together.

22:28.638 --> 22:31.724
You ran out into the back garden.
You were crying.

22:32.559 --> 22:34.894
You heard a noise
in the skies above you.

22:36.021 --> 22:39.106
The sound of bells, sleigh bells,
and that's when you saw me.

22:40.108 --> 22:41.802
You knew it wasn't a shooting star.

22:41.902 --> 22:45.154
That's just what your mother told you.
But you had proof.

22:46.740 --> 22:49.351
You found a gift in the garden,
a gift that I had left for you.

22:49.451 --> 22:51.619
What was it? Do you remember?

22:52.412 --> 22:53.981
Why don't you tell me?

22:54.081 --> 22:56.290
It was the most popular gift
of that year.

22:57.292 --> 22:58.793
A Rubik's cube.

22:59.586 --> 23:01.170
You still have it, don't you?

23:01.421 --> 23:03.464
Not because of me. Oh, no.

23:04.341 --> 23:07.968
No, you kept it because that was
the last family Christmas you ever had.

23:09.971 --> 23:11.806
How do you know that?

23:12.307 --> 23:14.016
Because he's Santa.

23:14.810 --> 23:16.936
Deep in your heart, you know who I am.

23:18.105 --> 23:20.856
Deep in my heart, you're a nutbag.

23:22.401 --> 23:23.859
(CHUCKLING)

23:25.404 --> 23:29.323
The reindeer have been moved
to a private area in Richmond Park.

23:29.449 --> 23:31.617
Go there. Seek out Dasher.

23:31.952 --> 23:33.702
He knows what to do.

23:34.037 --> 23:36.330
- Dasher speaks?
- He communicates.

23:36.456 --> 23:38.290
Right, that's it,
I've had enough of this.

23:38.417 --> 23:40.918
We haven't seen each other
in a very long time, Okay?

23:41.044 --> 23:44.239
And I wouldn't ask this if it wasn't
the most important job in the world.

23:44.339 --> 23:46.215
- Come on, we're going.
- We had a deal.

23:46.425 --> 23:49.343
What, you wanna spend our day
looking for a talking reindeer?

23:49.678 --> 23:52.012
- Yes.
- Okay, then, that's what we'll do.

23:52.139 --> 23:54.014
- Thank you.
- No, thank you.

23:54.266 --> 23:56.016
- Come on.
- One more thing.

23:57.436 --> 23:59.645
How do I survive in this place?

23:59.771 --> 24:02.106
Erm, stop pretending
to be Father Christmas.

24:02.315 --> 24:03.482
Steve.

24:04.359 --> 24:05.568
Go and see the barber.

24:05.902 --> 24:08.112
- Er, I can't change my look.
- For advice.

24:09.531 --> 24:11.115
Tell him I sent you.

24:16.037 --> 24:17.288
(BUZZING)

24:25.046 --> 24:27.256
Excuse me. Are you the barber?

24:27.716 --> 24:30.676
- No, I'm the vet.
- They keep animals here?

24:31.386 --> 24:33.888
Yeah, they keep
all sorts of animals in here.

24:34.014 --> 24:35.890
Do they keep reindeer?

24:36.475 --> 24:39.393
- Are you trying to be funny?
- No, I'm trying to find the barber.

24:39.811 --> 24:41.979
It's pretty obvious
I'm the barber, isn't it?

24:42.355 --> 24:44.732
Steve Anderson said
you'd be able to help me.

24:45.358 --> 24:48.068
- You know Steve?
- I know Steve very well.

24:49.029 --> 24:50.347
- Do one.
- Eh?

24:50.447 --> 24:51.655
Do one.

24:54.701 --> 24:56.645
Any friend of Steve's a friend of mine.

24:56.745 --> 25:01.290
Oh, that's great news!
A friend is exactly what I need.

25:01.708 --> 25:03.584
What can I do for you?

25:04.127 --> 25:06.670
Well, it's rather a long story.

25:07.464 --> 25:10.424
Take a seat, pops.
The one thing we've got in here is time.

25:10.675 --> 25:15.137
Well, I was born in Lapland
a long time ago.

25:15.805 --> 25:17.749
Neighbourhood I grew up in
was a small town

25:17.849 --> 25:20.267
in the Laughing Valley of Hohaho.

25:20.602 --> 25:22.796
Although my childhood was happy,

25:22.896 --> 25:27.441
one day an old woodcutter told me
about all the poverty in the world.

25:27.943 --> 25:31.362
And I was so shocked
that I went straight to Elf City.

25:31.780 --> 25:35.282
Now, the elves are wonderful
toy makers, as you know.

25:36.034 --> 25:38.327
So I went there with a mission,

25:38.620 --> 25:41.622
that on Christmas morning,
from that day forth,

25:41.831 --> 25:43.958
every child would get a toy.

25:44.709 --> 25:47.836
I know what you're thinking.
Where do the reindeer come in?

25:48.547 --> 25:50.965
STEVE: Right, so there's six reindeer,

25:51.466 --> 25:54.176
and they all look like, er, reindeer.

25:55.554 --> 25:59.014
None of them appear to be talking,
but... No, hang on, one second.

26:01.017 --> 26:03.211
Oh, no, he's just eating grass.

26:03.311 --> 26:05.813
Why are you acting like an idiot, Steve?

26:06.189 --> 26:09.468
You know, it wouldn't hurt you
to call me Dad once in a while,

26:09.568 --> 26:11.527
'Cause, like it or lump it,
that's what I am.

26:11.903 --> 26:13.153
Lump it.

26:14.656 --> 26:17.992
You're not going over the fence.
Get off the fence.

26:18.243 --> 26:21.120
Oi, you're not climbing over the fence.

26:22.664 --> 26:26.709
Right, that's it, mister. Me and you
are now officially no longer friends.

26:28.587 --> 26:31.072
So, as we speak, Steve and his son Tom

26:31.172 --> 26:33.575
are rescuing my head reindeer, Dasher,

26:33.675 --> 26:35.994
who will then lead them
to my new magic sleigh.

26:36.094 --> 26:39.179
They will then be able to fly in
and spring me from prison.

26:40.599 --> 26:43.684
Well, me first advice is
don't tell anyone about this.

26:44.019 --> 26:45.545
- Yeah, not in here.
- Okay.

26:45.645 --> 26:47.714
In fact, I think it might be better

26:47.814 --> 26:49.857
if we create a whole
new back story for you.

26:49.983 --> 26:52.761
You know, one where you won't end up
in a psychiatric unit.

26:52.861 --> 26:55.654
- You don't think they'll believe me?
- I'm positive they won't.

26:56.364 --> 27:00.868
So instead of "Santa Claus",
let's pretend your name's,

27:01.870 --> 27:05.039
I don't know, something like
Mad Jimmy Claws.

27:05.415 --> 27:09.376
You're a veteran safe cracker,
bank robber, all-round bad guy.

27:10.003 --> 27:11.587
Mad Jimmy Claws?

27:12.047 --> 27:13.839
Yeah. Do you like it?

27:14.090 --> 27:16.258
- I think it's horrible.
- It's supposed to be.

27:19.471 --> 27:21.388
Show me your gangster face.

27:21.556 --> 27:23.807
- My what?
- Your mean face.

27:24.768 --> 27:26.044
Hmm?

27:26.144 --> 27:27.963
Now, if you're gonna be
Mad Jimmy Claws, you've gotta be...

27:28.063 --> 27:30.397
- Mad.
- No, not mad crazy.

27:30.857 --> 27:32.107
Just mean.

27:32.442 --> 27:33.442
Mean.

27:34.110 --> 27:37.279
- No, mean.
- Mean.

27:38.239 --> 27:39.698
Don't ever do that again.

27:41.576 --> 27:45.162
Okay, so, Dasher, if you are here,

27:45.914 --> 27:48.832
your boss wants us
to spring him from prison,

27:49.584 --> 27:52.628
and he says that you would
know what to do.

27:59.260 --> 28:01.428
- Nothing.
- He might be shy.

28:01.596 --> 28:03.347
Or he might be a reindeer
that doesn't speak.

28:04.891 --> 28:07.434
Dasher, we're your friends.

28:07.811 --> 28:09.879
We're not going to hurt you.

28:09.979 --> 28:12.465
If you're here, just show yourself.

28:12.565 --> 28:14.274
(REINDEER GRUNTING)

28:15.985 --> 28:18.362
(REINDEER FARTS)

28:18.780 --> 28:20.864
(VERY LONG FART)

28:25.370 --> 28:28.288
Santa didn't say he spoke.
He said he communicated.

28:28.456 --> 28:30.833
That's not a communication.
That's a fart.

28:32.711 --> 28:34.696
Hello, reindeer.

28:34.796 --> 28:38.632
If any of you are trying to speak,
fart now.

28:39.634 --> 28:42.094
(FARTING)

28:43.596 --> 28:45.139
Oh, come on.

28:47.183 --> 28:49.977
If one of you is Dasher, fart now.

28:52.230 --> 28:53.605
Dasher's not here.

28:54.274 --> 28:57.651
- What, that's your proof?
- No.

29:03.324 --> 29:04.950
That's my proof.

29:05.493 --> 29:07.494
Santa has seven reindeer.

29:07.829 --> 29:10.330
(REINDEER FARTING)

29:10.665 --> 29:12.541
All right, so what does that mean?

29:12.751 --> 29:15.085
(SIREN WAILING)

29:16.504 --> 29:18.406
No, no, no, no. Quick, run!

29:18.506 --> 29:22.926
This is Sierra 15. We're in pursuit
of a man and child on suspicion of...

29:25.305 --> 29:29.141
- Why are we chasing them?
- Suspected reindeer rustling.

29:31.144 --> 29:32.337
(ENGINE FAILS TO START)

29:32.437 --> 29:35.590
- Oh, come on. Come on, come on.
- This van's rubbish.

29:35.690 --> 29:36.966
She's a bit rusty.

29:37.066 --> 29:39.094
But that's what happens when
you've been locked up for two years.

29:39.194 --> 29:40.652
- Come on!
- Hurry.

29:42.781 --> 29:44.364
(TYRES SCREECH)

29:49.704 --> 29:51.246
(SIREN WAILING)

29:55.668 --> 29:57.737
This is bad, Tom.
This is really, really bad.

29:57.837 --> 30:01.089
If I get caught, I'm going straight
back to... Oh, my!

30:01.466 --> 30:02.508
Dasher.

30:03.551 --> 30:06.162
It's him. Do you think
he can fly us out of here?

30:06.262 --> 30:07.914
No, I do not think
he can fly us out of here.

30:08.014 --> 30:10.140
- Dasher, can you fly?
- (DASHER FARTS)

30:10.266 --> 30:12.127
Will you stop asking
him questions, please?

30:12.227 --> 30:14.087
- It really is him, isn't it?
- Well, it is a reindeer, yes,

30:14.187 --> 30:15.187
I will give you that.

30:18.733 --> 30:20.677
I'm really sorry, I think we should
get back onto the road.

30:20.777 --> 30:22.528
If we stay on the grass,
we're going to be blocked in.

30:22.821 --> 30:25.739
- Gatehouse, this is Finkerton.
- MAN: (ON POLICE RADIO) Who?

30:25.907 --> 30:28.309
- Sergeant Finkerton.
- Finker what?

30:28.409 --> 30:30.687
Finkerton! Thames Valley Police.

30:30.787 --> 30:35.541
We have some traffic coming your way.
Be sure to stop it. Over!

30:39.879 --> 30:42.532
- What are we gonna do now?
- Well, we either stop or we don't.

30:42.632 --> 30:43.799
Don't!

30:52.100 --> 30:53.350
That was brilliant!

30:53.643 --> 30:56.103
Yes, but definitely not within
the terms of my parole.

30:57.021 --> 30:58.856
(SIREN WAILING)

31:06.739 --> 31:08.365
Not tough enough?

31:08.700 --> 31:10.450
Well, you're walking
like you need the toilet.

31:10.785 --> 31:12.119
All right.

31:13.746 --> 31:15.956
- How about this?
- Yeah, come on.

31:21.004 --> 31:22.963
- Fractionally better.
- Oh, good.

31:23.631 --> 31:28.176
Now, remember, anyone stares at you,
you stare right back at them, yeah?

31:28.511 --> 31:30.929
Don't be afraid,
but don't be stupid either.

31:31.389 --> 31:34.808
And if they won't budge,
tell 'em to get out of your face.

31:35.310 --> 31:36.727
Get out of your face!

31:36.895 --> 31:39.047
No, not get out of their face.
Get out of your face.

31:39.147 --> 31:40.757
Get out of their face.
Get out of your face.

31:40.857 --> 31:42.801
No. Get out of me face.

31:42.901 --> 31:44.693
- Get out of me face.
- That's it, yeah.

31:44.903 --> 31:46.387
- Yeah, Okay.
- Get out of me face.

31:46.487 --> 31:48.322
- Get out of me face.
- Get out of me face.

31:48.656 --> 31:51.033
- Yeah. Yeah, yeah.
- Very good.

31:51.492 --> 31:53.144
Right, in the chair.

31:53.244 --> 31:54.771
- Not...
- No, no, no, don't worry.

31:54.871 --> 31:57.873
I'm not gonna cut your beard.
Just a few finishing touches.

32:04.505 --> 32:06.715
- What's he doing?
- Stop the van.

32:07.008 --> 32:09.176
- Why?
- Stop the van.

32:12.597 --> 32:15.891
- I think he wants to get out.
- I wanna know how he got in.

32:28.237 --> 32:30.572
- TOM: Dad, hurry!
- STEVE: Wait up.

32:39.207 --> 32:40.624
Dasher!

32:44.545 --> 32:45.712
Dasher?

32:46.047 --> 32:48.590
Dasher! If that really is your name.

32:53.221 --> 32:54.388
Dasher!

33:40.852 --> 33:42.310
(CLICKING)

33:45.940 --> 33:49.151
(ENGINE WHIRRS AND STOPS)

33:52.321 --> 33:54.515
He really is Santa, isn't he?

33:54.615 --> 33:56.616
(SIREN WAILING)

33:57.160 --> 34:00.912
♪ (N.W.A. RAPPING STRAIGHT OUTTA COMPTON) ♪

34:02.915 --> 34:06.277
♪ Straight outta Compton
It's a crazy brother named Ice Cube ♪

34:06.377 --> 34:08.987
♪ From the stupid-dope gang
with a attitude ♪

34:09.088 --> 34:11.491
♪ When I'm called off, I got a sawed-off ♪

34:11.591 --> 34:13.659
♪ Kick knowledge
and bodies are hauled off ♪

34:13.760 --> 34:15.954
♪ You too, boy, if you get with me ♪

34:16.054 --> 34:18.206
♪ The police are gonna have
to come and get me ♪

34:18.306 --> 34:20.541
♪ Off your back,
that's how I'm goin' out ♪

34:20.641 --> 34:22.918
♪ For the sucka dumb brothas
that's showin' out ♪

34:23.018 --> 34:25.295
♪ Some start to mumble,
They wanna rumble ♪

34:25.396 --> 34:27.632
♪ Mix 'em and cook 'em
in a pot like gumbo ♪

34:27.732 --> 34:30.051
♪ Goin' off on everybody like that ♪

34:30.150 --> 34:33.221
♪ With bass that's droppin' in your face ♪

34:33.321 --> 34:35.030
♪ So give it up smooth... ♪

34:35.322 --> 34:36.531
An elf!

34:38.618 --> 34:40.409
What did you call me?

34:40.703 --> 34:44.081
Goodness. Why wasn't your absence
noted by your elf leader?

34:44.248 --> 34:45.608
What are you, a comedian?

34:45.708 --> 34:47.958
Are you part of Entwhistle's
theatre troupe?

34:48.210 --> 34:50.279
You'd best back up, crazy beard,

34:50.379 --> 34:52.407
before I slap that stupid grin
off your face.

34:52.507 --> 34:54.492
Wait a minute. I know what you're doing.

34:54.592 --> 34:56.577
You're doing your mean face.

34:56.677 --> 34:58.579
- My what?
- You're in character.

34:58.679 --> 35:00.013
He's good.

35:00.223 --> 35:02.682
Except I have a secret weapon
up my sleeve.

35:02.892 --> 35:06.186
A song that no elf
can resist singing along to.

35:06.813 --> 35:07.797
♪ (SINGING) ♪

35:07.897 --> 35:10.299
♪ Elves are good, elves are strong ♪

35:10.399 --> 35:12.218
♪ Making toys all night long ♪

35:12.318 --> 35:15.138
♪ In the snow, in the rain
Making toys is not a strain ♪

35:15.238 --> 35:17.140
♪ Working hard Stacking shelves ♪

35:17.240 --> 35:20.450
♪ We don't know cos we are elves
We are elves, we are... ♪

35:26.999 --> 35:28.708
You're not an elf, are you?

35:29.460 --> 35:31.211
No.

35:31.712 --> 35:34.214
Do you know who the smallest people
in the world are?

35:34.340 --> 35:36.049
- Not elves?
- Bullies.

35:36.926 --> 35:39.219
Inside, bullies are this small.

35:39.971 --> 35:43.056
I'm bigger than you, pal. Remember that.

35:45.434 --> 35:49.229
I don't think calling someone an elf
is an insult, do you?

35:50.064 --> 35:51.148
Yeah.

35:51.899 --> 35:54.401
Oi, Sally, what are you doing here?

35:54.902 --> 35:57.154
I thought you was escaping last night.

35:57.738 --> 36:00.824
- Is his name Sally?
- His prison name's Sally.

36:01.159 --> 36:04.119
Sally Gunnel, tunnel.
Cockney rhyming slang.

36:04.412 --> 36:07.414
On account he tells everyone he's
digging a tunnel to get out of here.

36:07.582 --> 36:09.291
He's as mad as you.

36:09.500 --> 36:10.959
(PHONE RINGS)

36:12.378 --> 36:13.545
Hello?

36:13.921 --> 36:16.590
Oh, hello, mate. Will you put
that Santa bloke on, please?

36:16.716 --> 36:19.509
What's going on?
What are you indulging this plan for?

36:19.760 --> 36:21.595
Just put him on, mate, will you?

36:22.305 --> 36:24.598
- SANTA: Hello. Steve?
- Oh, yeah. Hello. Um...

36:24.891 --> 36:27.976
So we found...
Well, we've got a reindeer

36:28.728 --> 36:32.314
and some sort of a, well, yeah,
it's a weird sleigh thing.

36:32.773 --> 36:34.717
Oh, Steve, that's great!

36:34.817 --> 36:36.109
What should I do now?

36:36.277 --> 36:39.362
Go to the rear of the vehicle,

36:39.864 --> 36:43.392
and there you'll find a compartment
with a picture of a,

36:43.492 --> 36:45.702
- well, a rather nice picture of a...
- Elf in a jumpsuit?

36:46.120 --> 36:48.830
Correct. Yes.
Now, there's a handle at the back.

36:48.998 --> 36:50.775
Now, make sure it's secure,

36:50.875 --> 36:53.111
but whatever you do
don't pull it all the way out

36:53.211 --> 36:56.364
because that way you'd lose the magic
powder, which would be a disaster.

36:56.464 --> 36:57.631
Uh...

36:58.966 --> 37:01.468
- Well, it's empty.
- No.

37:01.928 --> 37:05.805
Yeah. And all the... All the green
sort of dust stuff is all on the...

37:05.973 --> 37:07.224
It's all over the ground.

37:07.475 --> 37:09.726
Well, well, well.

37:09.977 --> 37:12.255
If it ain't the one they call Santa C.

37:12.355 --> 37:15.148
No, his name's Jimmy. Jimmy Claws.

37:15.358 --> 37:16.926
Who's talking to you, hairdresser?

37:17.026 --> 37:19.361
- I'm just making conversation.
- Well, don't.

37:20.613 --> 37:23.531
Steve, get the emergency kit
out of the glove compartment.

37:23.824 --> 37:26.534
Where's the glove compartment?
Where's the... Hello?

37:27.328 --> 37:28.495
STEVE: Hello?

37:32.208 --> 37:35.335
I've heard you do a right moody
impression of Father Christmas.

37:35.836 --> 37:37.379
Ho, ho, ho!

37:38.005 --> 37:40.575
I mean, no, no, no.

37:40.675 --> 37:43.995
I'm Jimmy Claws, not Santa Claus.

37:44.095 --> 37:46.346
- Get out of my face.
- What you say?

37:47.807 --> 37:50.517
I said, yes, I do a fine impression
of Santa Claus.

37:51.185 --> 37:54.145
- Show me.
- What would you like me to say?

37:54.480 --> 37:58.441
- What does FC normally say?
- "FC". I like that!

37:59.068 --> 38:01.804
INMATE: "Hello, little girl.
Have you been good?

38:01.904 --> 38:03.363
"Or you been really, really naughty?"

38:04.365 --> 38:08.477
No, no, no. Ho, ho, ho!
Merry Christmas, everyone.

38:08.577 --> 38:10.188
Merry Christmas.

38:10.288 --> 38:11.939
Now you're talking.

38:12.039 --> 38:14.165
- You got the job.
- What job?

38:14.375 --> 38:17.195
We're having a Christmas Eve party
later for the kids and the families.

38:17.295 --> 38:18.821
We do it every year.

38:18.921 --> 38:23.091
I want you to dress up
as Father Christmas and do a turn.

38:23.342 --> 38:25.885
You know, we'll even have the guards
get you a costume.

38:26.554 --> 38:28.930
- Would you do that for me?
- Oh, yes!

38:30.391 --> 38:33.226
I mean, sure, I'll do that for you.

38:53.414 --> 38:54.539
If all else fails.

39:04.717 --> 39:09.512
If all else fails,
go to Hermey's Tower, Suffolk.

39:14.935 --> 39:16.754
- We can't go to Suffolk.
- Why?

39:16.854 --> 39:19.507
'Cause you've gotta be home at 4:00
and I've got a parole meeting at 5:00.

39:19.607 --> 39:23.094
- But we're trying to save Christmas.
- And I'm trying to stay out of prison.

39:23.194 --> 39:24.387
So you're just gonna quit?

39:24.487 --> 39:27.364
I can't miss my parole meeting, Tom.
It's impossible. I'm sorry.

39:27.656 --> 39:29.684
Then Mum was right about you.

39:29.784 --> 39:32.077
What do you mean? Why?
What did Mum say about me?

39:32.495 --> 39:35.497
That you'd build me up with promises
and then let me down.

39:35.706 --> 39:39.125
That's a very nasty thing to say,
and it's not true.

39:40.461 --> 39:42.280
Well, no, actually, it is true.

39:42.380 --> 39:45.116
I am immensely unreliable
and I always let people down,

39:45.216 --> 39:48.077
which is precisely the reason
why Santa would never choose me

39:48.177 --> 39:50.303
for this so-called mission.

39:50.513 --> 39:52.999
Yeah? Well, he did.
So he must have had a good reason.

39:53.099 --> 39:55.642
All I wanted today
was a chance to be a proper dad.

39:56.811 --> 39:58.937
Do you have any idea how long
I've been waiting to see you?

39:59.313 --> 40:01.272
Two years, one month and three days.

40:02.316 --> 40:03.817
That's right.

40:04.151 --> 40:06.277
Santa's relying on you, Dad.

40:13.828 --> 40:15.829
- (CROAKING)
- (LAUGHS)

40:16.956 --> 40:18.415
