Hello, Ruth. Do come in.

43:12.756 --> 43:14.882
- Have you bought me a gift?
- No.

43:15.342 --> 43:17.786
That's my toad.
He spends Christmas with me.

43:17.886 --> 43:22.098
Steve Anderson, on the other hand,
is going back to prison.

43:24.143 --> 43:26.686
It would seem you do
have a gift for me after all.

43:28.188 --> 43:30.148
The name of our suspect.

43:30.649 --> 43:33.802
- (ENGINE SPUTTERS)
- Oh, no, no, no, no, no.

43:33.902 --> 43:35.930
- This is not good.
- What is it, Dad?

43:36.030 --> 43:38.281
No, it's all right. Don't worry.
Just stay there.

43:39.742 --> 43:41.326
(STEAM HISSES)

43:41.744 --> 43:43.786
TOM: Will it be all right, Dad?

43:45.873 --> 43:47.123
(COUGHS)

43:52.880 --> 43:54.964
(POLICE RADIO CHATTER)

44:06.143 --> 44:08.462
Look, the police are here.
Let me deal with it.

44:08.562 --> 44:11.481
Don't say anything. And will
you close those curtains, please?

44:18.447 --> 44:19.989
Hello, Officer.

44:20.783 --> 44:23.409
- Looks like your head gasket's blown.
- Yeah.

44:23.952 --> 44:25.953
- Yeah, yeah, yeah, yeah.
- All right, little man?

44:26.580 --> 44:29.275
- We'll be fine, thank you.
- You got cover?

44:29.375 --> 44:32.403
No, but a friend has got a breakdown
vehicle, so I'll just call him.

44:32.503 --> 44:35.588
Okay, well, my advice would be
to sit up on the bank.

44:36.090 --> 44:39.285
- Don't want anyone crashing into you.
- No, we don't. Thank you, sir.

44:39.385 --> 44:41.135
- Right.
- All right, you have a good

44:41.345 --> 44:43.763
- (DASHER BELLOWS)
- day.

44:45.182 --> 44:47.058
(THUDDING AND CLATTERING)

44:48.852 --> 44:51.046
So what have you got in there?

44:51.146 --> 44:53.022
A... A dog.

44:53.440 --> 44:54.967
Yeah? What kind of dog?

44:55.067 --> 44:56.943
(CLATTERING)

44:57.111 --> 44:59.737
- A... A very big one.
- (JINGLING)

45:26.056 --> 45:28.474
That's a funny-looking dog.

45:29.226 --> 45:31.712
Oh, God! Oh, no!

45:31.812 --> 45:35.857
No, no, no, no, no, no, no, no!
Bad deer. Bad deer.

45:36.483 --> 45:38.969
- Is he dead?
- No, he is not dead.

45:39.069 --> 45:40.820
Don't even say that.

45:41.530 --> 45:44.157
But he is gonna wake up in 10 minutes
with a very sore head.

45:44.283 --> 45:46.075
What are we gonna do?

45:47.327 --> 45:50.064
It'll be fine, Dad. He'll understand.

45:50.164 --> 45:51.664
No, he won't.

45:52.458 --> 45:54.834
♪ (THE SATURDAYS SINGING CHRISTMAS WRAPPING) ♪

